The experience of any immigrant, and the complex attitudes that the immigrant experience generates both towards the new culture and the old\u003cbr /\u003e* The deplorable status of women in Bangladesh\u003cbr /\u003e* The wrenching realization that one is married to an idiot\u003cbr /\u003e* The nature of marriage itself\u003cbr /\u003e* The hypocrites that exist in any culture and religion (very ironic that the shameless usurer in the book is named Mrs. Islam)\u003cbr /\u003e* The way that living in a specific slice of history influences one's opinions and values\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eAlthough this book is rather long, the author probably needed the length to address her varied themes. It's a serious book, but often hilarious. It's uplifting, because it speaks of women's empowerment. And it kindled a desire in me to learn more about Bangladesh and its history -- and perhaps go there some day.\u003cbr /\u003e","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/889171?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/806742433"},"likeCount":33,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":5,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.QnOe5ZAqsAp3fm8yssB0JA":{"id":"kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.QnOe5ZAqsAp3fm8yssB0JA","__typename":"Book"},"User:7477266":{"id":7477266,"__typename":"User","legacyId":7477266,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1433820623i/7477266._UX200_CR0,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":387,"viewableName":"Sarah","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/7477266-sarah","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":124},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.Iz_MTXYZlL-k9gq6pVs2jw":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.Iz_MTXYZlL-